00059 // Setup for Windows DLL export/import. When building the V8 DLL the
00060 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When building a program which uses
00061 // the V8 DLL USING_V8_SHARED needs to be defined. When either building the V8
00062 // static library or building a program which uses the V8 static library neither
00063 // BUILDING_V8_SHARED nor USING_V8_SHARED should be defined.
00064 // The reason for having both V8EXPORT and V8EXPORT_INLINE is that classes which
00065 // have their code inside this header file need to have __declspec(dllexport)
00066 // when building the DLL but cannot have __declspec(dllimport) when building
00067 // a program which uses the DLL.
00068 #if defined(BUILDING_V8_SHARED) && defined(USING_V8_SHARED)
00069 #error both BUILDING_V8_SHARED and USING_V8_SHARED are set - please check the\
00070   build configuration to ensure that at most one of these is set
00071 #endif
00072 
00073 #ifdef BUILDING_V8_SHARED
00074 #define V8EXPORT __declspec(dllexport)
00075 #define V8EXPORT_INLINE __declspec(dllexport)
00076 #elif USING_V8_SHARED
00077 #define V8EXPORT __declspec(dllimport)
00078 #define V8EXPORT_INLINE
00079 #else
00080 #define V8EXPORT
00081 #define V8EXPORT_INLINE
00082 #endif  // BUILDING_V8_SHARED
00083 
00084 #else  // _WIN32
00085 
00086 #include <stdint.h>
00087 
00088 // Setup for Linux shared library export. There is no need to distinguish
00089 // between building or using the V8 shared library, but we should not
00090 // export symbols when we are building a static library.
00091 #if defined(__GNUC__) && (__GNUC__ >= 4) && defined(V8_SHARED)
00092 #define V8EXPORT __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
00093 #define V8EXPORT_INLINE __attribute__ ((visibility("default")))
00094 #else  // defined(__GNUC__) && (__GNUC__ >= 4)
00095 #define V8EXPORT
00096 #define V8EXPORT_INLINE
00097 #endif  // defined(__GNUC__) && (__GNUC__ >= 4)
00098 
00099 #endif  // _WIN32

03145 // Tag information for HeapObject.
03146 const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
03147 const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
03148 const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
03149 
03150 // Tag information for Smi.
03151 const int kSmiTag = 0;
03152 const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
03153 const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
03154 
03155 template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiConstants;
03156 
03157 // Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
03158 template <> struct SmiConstants<4> {
03159   static const int kSmiShiftSize = 0;
03160   static const int kSmiValueSize = 31;
03161   static inline int SmiToInt(internal::Object* value) {
03162     int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
03163     // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
03164     return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
03165   }
03166 };
03167 
03168 // Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
03169 template <> struct SmiConstants<8> {
03170   static const int kSmiShiftSize = 31;
03171   static const int kSmiValueSize = 32;
03172   static inline int SmiToInt(internal::Object* value) {
03173     int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
03174     // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
03175     return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
03176   }
03177 };
03178 
03179 const int kSmiShiftSize = SmiConstants<sizeof(void*)>::kSmiShiftSize;
03180 const int kSmiValueSize = SmiConstants<sizeof(void*)>::kSmiValueSize;

03199 class Internals {
03200  public:
03201 
03202   // These values match non-compiler-dependent values defined within
03203   // the implementation of v8.
03204   static const int kHeapObjectMapOffset = 0;
03205   static const int kMapInstanceTypeOffset = sizeof(void*) + sizeof(int);
03206   static const int kStringResourceOffset =
03207       InternalConstants<sizeof(void*)>::kStringResourceOffset;
03208 
03209   static const int kProxyProxyOffset = sizeof(void*);
03210   static const int kJSObjectHeaderSize = 3 * sizeof(void*);
03211   static const int kFullStringRepresentationMask = 0x07;
03212   static const int kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag = 0x02;
03213 
03214   static const int kJSObjectType = 0x9f;
03215   static const int kFirstNonstringType = 0x80;
03216   static const int kProxyType = 0x85;
03217 
03218   static inline bool HasHeapObjectTag(internal::Object* value) {
03219     return ((reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) & kHeapObjectTagMask) ==
03220             kHeapObjectTag);
03221   }
03222 
03223   static inline bool HasSmiTag(internal::Object* value) {
03224     return ((reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) & kSmiTagMask) == kSmiTag);
03225   }
03226 
03227   static inline int SmiValue(internal::Object* value) {
03228     return SmiConstants<sizeof(void*)>::SmiToInt(value);
03229   }
03230 
03231   static inline int GetInstanceType(internal::Object* obj) {
03232     typedef internal::Object O;
03233     O* map = ReadField<O*>(obj, kHeapObjectMapOffset);
03234     return ReadField<uint8_t>(map, kMapInstanceTypeOffset);
03235   }
03236 
03237   static inline void* GetExternalPointer(internal::Object* obj) {
03238     if (HasSmiTag(obj)) {
03239       return obj;
03240     } else if (GetInstanceType(obj) == kProxyType) {
03241       return ReadField<void*>(obj, kProxyProxyOffset);
03242     } else {
03243       return NULL;
03244     }
03245   }
03246 
03247   static inline bool IsExternalTwoByteString(int instance_type) {
03248     int representation = (instance_type & kFullStringRepresentationMask);
03249     return representation == kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag;
03250   }

03254     uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;
03255     return *reinterpret_cast<T*>(addr);
03256   }

03400 Local<Value> Object::UncheckedGetInternalField(int index) {
03401   typedef internal::Object O;
03402   typedef internal::Internals I;
03403   O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
03404   if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType) {
03405     // If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case,
03406     // we know where to find the internal fields and can return the
03407     // value directly.
03408     int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (sizeof(void*) * index);
03409     O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
03410     O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(value);
03411     return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
03412   } else {
03413     return Local<Value>();
03414   }
